rComments: Chelsea is very funny, extremely helpful, and loves her subject. Go to office hours, she'll give you research paper source help! Lots of reading, but hey, it's anthro. Take home midterm and final, research paper, reading responses. Fun class, learned a lot.

She is enthusiastic about the material and lectures were interesting.  The amount of reading was reasonable and useful.  The assignments were difficult and graded hard.  Attendance counted for participation points in your grade.

She makes classes fun and interesting.  She works hard to communicate materials aclearly, is willing to work with students and always makes herself available.  She expects a lot from her students but gives a lot in return.

Chelsea is a very fun funny (and fun) professor is a terribly and dry subject. If you need to take an archaeology elective (poor anthro majors), you should at least take it with her - she'll inject a modicum  of interesting material. Come to class prepared and make a small effort to participate; she'll reward you in her gradebook.
She is extremely helpful and willing to work with you. It felt more like a partnership with an well-educated mentor. I highly recommend taking a class with her!
